## License Scope

This build system and configuration files (scripts, profiles, documentation)
are provided under the MIT License.

## Third-Party Software

The resulting ISO includes software packages with their own respective licenses:

### ArchLinux Distribution
- **Package sources (PKGBUILDs)**: 0BSD License (as of recent ArchLinux policy)
- **Packaged software**: Various licenses (GPL, MIT, BSD, etc.) as per individual packages
- See: https://www.archlinux.org/

### Rust Utilities
- **uutils-coreutils**: MIT License - https://github.com/uutils/coreutils
- **ripgrep**: MIT or Unlicense
- **fd**: MIT or Apache-2.0
- **bat**: MIT or Apache-2.0
- **eza**: MIT
- **procs**: MIT
- **bottom**: MIT
- **dust**: Apache-2.0
- **zoxide**: MIT
- **starship**: ISC
- **tealdeer**: MIT or Apache-2.0
- **sd**: MIT
- **tokei**: MIT or Apache-2.0
- **hyperfine**: MIT or Apache-2.0

### License Compatibility

The MIT License is compatible with:
- All included Rust utilities (MIT, Apache-2.0, ISC, Unlicense)
- ArchLinux package source licensing (0BSD)
- GPL-licensed software (MIT can be included in GPL projects)

## User Responsibility

Users are responsible for complying with all applicable licenses when using
the generated ISO or any included software packages. Please refer to the
individual package license files for complete license information.

For package license information in the installed system:
```bash
pacman -Qi <package-name>  # Shows license information
```

